\section{Summary.}

1.  In considered 2D lattice in the case of a diagonal field, many effects have been found which were shown in the article \citet{PhysRevB.85.155124} for a diagonal field on a hypercubic lattice:

a) Population inversion at the pulse with $A_{max} =\pi\sqrt{2}$ which shift maximum of momentum distribution from $\Gamma$ to M (Figures: \ref{fig:E_tot}a,c; \ref{fig:FS_u2_A_max}a,c,e; \ref{fig:FS_u3_A_max}a,c,e).

b) Appearance of a population inversion and dependence of the total energy for different amplitudes of the vector potential (Figure \ref{fig:E_tot_A}), the Coulomb interaction and the pulse width (Figure \ref{fig:E_tot_tau}).

c) Relaxation of the momentum distribution after the pulse with amplitude $0.8A_{max}$ (Figure \ref{fig:md_u2_08A_relaxation}a,c,e).

2.  Relaxation time of the momentum distribution decreases with increasing Coulomb interaction. This can be seen from the comparison Figure \ref{fig:md_u2_A_max_relaxation} and Figure \ref{fig:md_u3_A_max_relaxation}.

3.  For a field in the Y-direction. Such a field does not create a population inversion for considered parameters (Figures: \ref{fig:E_tot_A}, \ref{fig:E_tot_tau}). It was shown how momentum distribution and Fermi surface change for different values of vector potential, Coulomb interaction and the pulse width before and after the pulse.

4.  For a field in the Y-direction Fermi surface forms a gap (Figures: \ref{fig:FS_u2_A_max}f, \ref{fig:FS_u3_A_max}d, \ref{fig:FS_u2_08A_max}f). From the beginning of the formation of the gap Fermi surface changes strongly and at the end of the relaxation it looks like before the pulse.
